                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Merry</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San José, Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-07-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 20, 1906</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Minister Merry acknowledges department’s cipher telegram of 18th, and remarks
                    that Nicaraguan and Costa Rican representation <pb facs="0955" n="849"
                        xml:id="pg_849"/> is entirely complimentary without votes or influence.
                    Nicaragua was invited by Salvador without advising Mr. Merry. The belligerents
                    are fully controlling the discussion, in accordance with the President’s
                    message. Conference results in a treaty of peace, as has been duly advised in
                    joint telegram with Minister Combs.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
